<subSubSection id="C3396559FFAAFF93F30796C3FAB7BE0E" pageId="15" pageNumber="324" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9C36D2FFAAFF93F30796C3FAB7BE0E" blockId="15.[813,1452,1210,1363]" pageId="15" pageNumber="324">
<emphasis id="B957EAC0FFAAFF93F30796C3FC74BF8E" bold="true" box="[813,929,1210,1234]" pageId="15" pageNumber="324">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Medium sized, broadly oval species (body length 
<quantity id="4CDB9B37FFAAFF93F30796A3FC66BFAE" box="[813,947,1242,1266]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.45" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="15" pageNumber="324" unit="mm" value="4.45" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.4">4.4–4.5 mm</quantity>
). Elytra with subbasal testaceous band divided longitudinally into separate spots (
<figureCitation id="13182A57FFAAFF93F4839683FB2FBE4E" box="[1193,1274,1274,1298]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[135,179,2064,2086]" captionTargetBox="[168,1456,189,2051]" captionTargetId="figure-8@4.[133,1476,180,2059]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 10–17. Habitus of Laccophilus: 10, L. mahakamensis; 11, L. mazzoldii, new species; 12, L. nusatenggaraensis, new species; 13, L. schillhammeri, new species; 14, L. stastnyi, new species; 15, L. tobaensis; 16, L. tonkinensis; 17, L. wittmeri. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5385202" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5385202/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="324">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Apical part of median lobe rather short, almost subparallel; in lateral view with dorsal side only very slightly curved (
<figureCitation id="13182A57FFAAFF93F52E9743FA83BE0E" box="[1284,1366,1338,1362]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[113,157,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[120,1445,189,1990]" captionTargetId="figure-10@7.[110,1454,186,1997]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 18–35. Median lobe in lateral view: 18, Laccophilus aurofasciatus; 19, L. auropictus; 20, L. ceylonicus; 21, L. elegans; 22, L. girardi; 23, L. hendrichi, new species; 24, L. jaechi, new species; 25, L. javanicus; 26, L. kalimantanensis, new species; 27, L. komareki, new species. 28, L. mahakamensis; 29, L. mazzoldii, new species; 30, L. nusatenggaraensis, new species; 31, L. schillhammeri, new species; 32, L. stastnyi, new species; 33, L. tobaensis; 34, L. tonkinensis; 35, L. wittmeri. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5385204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5385204/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="324">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3396559FFAAFF93F3079703FA42BEEE" pageId="15" pageNumber="324" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9C36D2FFAAFF93F3079703FA42BEEE" blockId="15.[813,1452,1402,1458]" pageId="15" pageNumber="324">
<emphasis id="B957EAC0FFAAFF93F3079703FC6ABECE" bold="true" box="[813,959,1402,1426]" pageId="15" pageNumber="324">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species was described and is so far known only from northern 
<collectingRegion id="49E7F830FFAAFF93F42E97E3FB88BEEE" box="[1028,1117,1434,1458]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="15" pageNumber="324">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B23FFAAFF93F44797E3FACABEEE" author="Brancucci M" box="[1133,1311,1434,1458]" firstAuthor="Brancucci" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Arbeiten aus dem Museum G. Frey" pageId="15" pageNumber="324" pagination="241 - 426" part="31 / 32" refId="ref15135" refString="Brancucci M (1983) Revision des especes est-palearctiques, orientales et australiennes du genre Laccophilus (Col. Dytiscidae). Entomologische Arbeiten aus dem Museum G. Frey, 31 / 32: 241 - 426." title="Revision des especes est-palearctiques, orientales et australiennes du genre Laccophilus (Col. Dytiscidae)" type="journal article" year="1983">Brancucci, 1983</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation id="13182A57FFAAFF93F51397E3FA5CBEEE" box="[1337,1417,1434,1458]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="9.[113,157,2093,2115]" captionTargetBox="[141,1427,190,2077]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs. 40–41. Distribution of the species of the Laccophilus javanicus group" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5385208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5385208/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="324">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
